<H3> <TI>   Transportation, Communication Protocol Signed With Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transportation, Communication Protocol Signed With Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0704102094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0910 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0704102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Moscow, April 7 (A.A.) -- Turkey and Russia on 
Wednesday signed a protocol during a joint economic commission 
meeting concerning energy, transportation, communications and 
other fields. 
  The signatories of the protocol were Housing and Public 
Works 
Minister Onur Kumbaracibasi and Russian Economic Affairs 
Minister Oleg Davydov. 
  The protocol foresees improving cooperation in 
transportation, communication and other fields. 
  Kumbaracibasi speaking during the signing ceremony said the 
two sides reviewed the subjects in a positive atmosphere. 
  Kumbaracibasi said Turkish-Russian relations improve 
day-by-day and these two sides have the goodwill to overcome the 
existing problems in economic fields. 
  Davydov said with the protocol, trade volume between Turkey 
and Russia will reach 2 billion U.S. dollars. 
  'Turkey will continue to be our best trade partner,' Davydov 
said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

