<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraqi, Russian Communist Party Officials Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi, Russian Communist Party Officials Hold Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0604164594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1520 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0604164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 6 Apr (INA)--'Abd-al-Ghani 'Abd-al-Ghafur, 
member of the Iraq Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party, 
met here today with Valentin Kuznetsov, first deputy leader of 
the Russian Communist Party [name and title as received]. 
  During the meeting, 'Abd-al-Ghafur gave a detailed 
explanation on the stable situation in Iraq as well as the Iraqi 
people's support for President Saddam Husayn's leadership and 
their insistence on breaking the economic blockade through 
patience, jihad, and continued progress and construction. He 
also pointed to the positive development in Russia's position at 
the Security Council, and stressed the need for Russia to adopt 
more effective positions, and for the Russian parties work 
through the Parliament, the government, and popular bodies to 
help lift the economic blockade on Iraq and implement Paragraph 
22 of Resolution 687. 
  Kuznetsov reiterated the Russian Communist Party's position, 
which supports the Iraqi leadership and people. He lauded the 
Iraqi people's achievements under President Saddam Husayn, and 
voiced his party's readiness to do further work on the 
parliamentary and popular levels in order to lift the economic 
blockade on Iraq. 

</TEXT>

