<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreements Planned With Russian Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604152794 Yerevan SNARK in English 0855 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, April 6 (SNARK) -- Georgia takes an active 
part in the process of ensuring cooperation among the security 
services of the Black Sea basin countries. This declaration was 
made yesterday by the Chairman of State Security Service of 
Georgia (the former Ministry of Security) Igor Giorgadze at the 
press-conference held in Tbilisi. 
  In his words, the relations with Russia are extremely 
important here. He said, in particular, that the Service headed 
by him is going to conclude agreements on cooperation with 
Russian counterintelligence and reconnaissance services, 
President's Security and Russian frontier troops in the near 
future. 
  Georgia counts on Russia's understanding of mutual interests 
in the cause of ensuring security of the two states, concluded 
Igor Giorgadze. 

