<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mediator on Karabakh Issue Meets With Aliyev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mediator on Karabakh Issue Meets With Aliyev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704132994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1048 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On night of April 7 Vladimir Kazimirov, special 
representative of the Russian president and Ambassador at large, 
who is a mediator in the settlement of the Armenian-Azerbaijani 
conflict, met with President Heydar Aliyev in Baku. The meeting 
was held behind closed doors. There is no information about the 
details of this meeting. 
  On the eve of the meeting Kazimirov reported in his 
interview 
with journalists that the major goal of his present visit to 
Baku is the clarification of the position of the Azerbaijani 
party to the renewed variant of the Russian plan aimed at the 
political settlement of the Karabakh conflict. 
  The Russian plan, in particular, provides for a cease-fire 
and cessation of hostilities to be followed by withdrawal of the 
troops from the territories occupied in the course of 
hostilities, restoration of communications, return of refugees 
to their permanent place of residence, and, at the third stage, 
political negotiations on the legal status of Nagorno-Karabakh. 

</TEXT>

