  [Text] Today the Federation Council approved a decree by 
the Russian president on introducing a state of emergency in the 
conflict zone on the territory of North Ossetia and Ingushetia. 
The discussion was held behind closed doors and lasted four 
hours. However, the issue was not settled, and the problem will 
be discussed tomorrow. 
  After the session, Ingush President Ruslan Aushev stated to 
an ITAR-TASS correspondent that he may leave it. He disagrees 
with the approaches used to settle the conflict. North Ossetian 
President Akhsarbek Galazov refrained from commenting on the 
content of the presidential decree. 

