<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Supports Latvian Protest Against Edict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Supports Latvian Protest Against Edict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604220894 Vilnius Radio Vilnius International Service in 
Lithuanian 2100 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius International Service </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Unilateral action taken by Russia aimed at setting 
up military bases in Latvia against the will of a sovereign 
state run counter to the principles of international law and 
obligations -- which had been undertaken by Russia as a member 
of the United Nations and a participant of the CSCE -- the 
statement of the Lithuanian Foreign Ministry reads. 
  On 5 April, Russian President Boris Yeltsin signed an edict 
according to which approval is given to the proposal by the 
Russian Ministry of Defense to set up Russian military bases on 
the territories of CIS countries and Latvia for testing new 
weapons and military equipment. 
  Lithuania supports in every possible way Latvia's desire to 
have the Russian troops withdrawn from her territory and 
declares that only the Republic of Latvia has the right to 
decide the military basis of what state can be deployed on her 
territory, the statement of the Lithuanian Foreign Ministry 
reads. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

