<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Text of Yeltsin Directive on Bases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Text of Yeltsin Directive on Bases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0704081594 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 7 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0704081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Directive of the Russian Federation President" No. 174-rp, </F>
signed by Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin and dated 5 
April 1994] 
  [Text] To agree with the proposal of the Russian Ministry 
of Defense, coordinated with the Russian Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs, on the creation of military bases of the Russian 
Federation Armed Forces on the territories of the member states 
of the CIS and the Latvian Republic in order to ensure the 
security of the Russian Federation and the aforementioned 
states, and also for testing new arms and military equipment. 
  The Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, jointly with the 
Russian Ministry of Defense and other interested Russian 
Federation ministries and departments, are to conduct talks on 
this question with member states of the CIS and the Latvian 
Republic, and formulate the agreements reached in appropriate 
documents. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] 5 April 1994 
  No. 174-rp 

</TEXT>

