<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Suspends Ingushetia President's Ruling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Suspends Ingushetia President's Ruling </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0704145194 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 7 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0704145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 659 of the Russian Federation President "On </F>
Suspending the Validity of Edict No. 63 of the Republic of 
Ingushetia President `On the Republic of Ingushetia Minister of 
Security' Dated 21 March 1994"; dated Moscow, the Kremlin, 5 
April 1994 and signed by Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin] 
  [Text] In connection with the publication of Edict No. 63 
of the Republic of Ingushetia President "On the Republic of 
Ingushetia Minister of Security," dated 21 March 1994, which 
contravenes Article 71 of the Russian Federation Constitution 
and the Russian Federation President's Edict No. 19 of 5 January 
1994 "On Ratifying the Statute on the Russian Federation Federal 
Counterintelligence Service," I decree that: 
  1. Guided by Articles 80 and 85 of the Russian Federation 
Constitution, the validity of Edict No. 63 of the Republic of 
Ingushetia president "On the Republic of Ingushetia Security 
Minister" dated 21 March 1994 is to be suspended. 
  2. A proposal shall be made to Republic of Ingushetia 
President R.S. Aushev that he bring the aforementioned edict 
into line with the Russian Federation Constitution. 
  3. This edict comes into force from the moment of signing. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  Moscow, the Kremlin 
  5 April 1994 
  No. 659 

</TEXT>

