<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Appoints Shakhray Deputy Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Appoints Shakhray Deputy Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704120494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1135 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow April 7 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin has appointed Nationalities Minister Sergey Shakhray as 
deputy prime minister, the press service of the president 
reported today. Thus the number of deputy prime ministers 
amounted to six, including one first deputy. 

</TEXT>

