<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Supports Kazannik </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Supports Kazannik </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604174994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1518 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 6 Apr -- A form of words releasing Aleksey 
Kazannik from the post of Russian procurator general has failed 
to gain a majority of votes. The chairman of the teller's 
commission reported that 68 deputies in the Federation Council 
voted in favor of releasing him, while 74 voted against. 
  According to the standing orders adopted today by the 
Federation Council, the procurator general is deemed to be 
released from his duties if a majority of the total number of 
deputies in the Federation Council votes in favor of that. The 
total number of deputies in the chamber is 174. Voting slips 
were taken by 145 people today. Therefore, over half of the 
total number of deputies did not vote in favor of releasing 
Kazannikov, the members of the teller's commission concluded. 
However, the chamber was unable today to formulate a legally 
satisfactory decision on the issue. It was decided to do that 
tomorrow. The sitting ended at that point. 

</TEXT>

