<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Literally a few minutes before the start of our 
program, the Information Television Agency received a statement 
issued by Russian President Boris Yeltsin, which expresses 
regret that the results of the voting in the Federation Council 
did not make it possible to adopt a final decision on the 
appointment of a procurator general. This outcome, the document 
says, does not mean that the former procurator general will 
return to his post; and thus Aleksey Ilyushenko will remain as 
acting procurator general. The president also considers that the 
Federation Council deputies who have been invested with the 
people's trust will find a suitable way out of the situation 
that has arisen. 

</TEXT>

