  [Text] The Federation Council Chairman Vladimir Shumeyko 
told the deputies on Wednesday that his meeting with President 
Yeltsin, scheduled for April 6, would not take place. Commenting 
on the media reports about joint Russian-American military 
exercises to be held in the Urals next summer, Shumeyko said 
that the Federation Council must not be guided by reports 
appearing in the press. 

