<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communist Leader: U.S. Underestimates Russian Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Communist Leader: U.S. Underestimates Russian Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704121494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1134 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704121494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Barsukov] </F>
  [Text] Washington April 7 TASS -- Russian communist leader 
Gennadiy Zyuganov said his party and its allies would do 
everything to achieve national reconciliation and accord in 
Russia. He stressed that it is impossible to stabilise the 
situation in the country without it, he said. 
  Zyuganov noted that, during his latest meetings with 
high-ranking representatives of the administration, he had got 
an impression that the U.S. leadership realised Russia's 
problems and a new policy toward Russia was needed. At the same 
time, the administration underestimates the processes underway 
in Russia, he said. 
  According to Zyuganov, "the situation in Russia is going 
from 
bad to worse as before". The state has become a "communicating 
court" and does not fulfil its functions. The crime rate has 
reached the scale of the post-civil-war period. The power is 
concentrated in the hands of one man, the Russian president, 
whose powers are four times as much as the U.S. President has. 
It lets those who have no powers and play a role of "collective 
baron" "conduct the Russian civil strife". The situation in 
many important spheres in the country is critical. Even missile 
systems do not undergo some necessary operations in time, he 
said. 
  According to the Russian communist leader, any democracy is 
out of the question if there is no bread, water and heating. 
The stabilisation of the situation is the main task requiring 
coordinated efforts, of the international community in 
particular. The further confrontation in Russia will lead to a 
national tragedy. 
  Zyuganov noted that a rather big central-leftist bloc had 
formed in the State Duma which can propose its own programme to 
overcome the crisis in the country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

