<H3> <TI>   Government Plans Obligatory Insurance Law by Autumn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Plans Obligatory Insurance Law by Autumn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604180694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1602 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0604180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow April 6 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin signed a decree on Wednesday obliging the government to 
submit a draft law on the basic principles of obligatory 
insurance in Russia to the State Duma by September 1, 1994. The 
draft law will have to define the concept of obligatory 
insurance and its goals. The cabinet has also been instructed 
to prepare and submit draft laws on the procedure for and terms 
of specific forms of obligatory insurance. 
  The move aims at ensuring civil liberties and rights granted 
to the people of Russia by the Constitution, the presidential 
press service said. 

