<H3> <TI>   Government Plans Tighter Control of Oil Exports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Plans Tighter Control of Oil Exports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604112394 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
0400 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] By the middle of the current year, all oil 
exporters will be determined by the Russian Government. This 
matter was previously dealt with by the Ministry of Foreign 
Economic Relations. This decision has been made by the 
government commission on operational issues. In the opinion of 
experts at the RIKA news agency, the government commission's 
decision is connected with the fact that the state budget 
received just $6.9 billion of the $8.5 billion revenue from 
state oil export quotas. In order to prevent petrodollars 
leaking abroad, a group of authorized banks will soon be 
entrusted with the handling of oil exporters' accounts. 

</TEXT>

