<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Proceeding in `Calm' Atmosphere </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks Proceeding in `Calm' Atmosphere </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704223894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1726 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704223894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Vladimir Taranov and </F>
Boris Krivoshey] 
  [Text] Moscow April 7 TASS -- The Moscow round of talks 
between the Tajik Government and anti-government opposition is 
proceeding in calm and businesslike atmosphere. Both 
negotiating teams demonstrate a constructive attitude towards 
problems tackled by the talks, spokesman for the Russian Foreign 
Ministry Grigoriy Karasin told a briefing on Thursday. 
  Nobody is under illusion that the current Tajik negotiations 
will immediately disentangle all knots, which is to take 
strained and ponderous efforts. Some recent reports by the mass 
media are based on off-the-record statements and do not tend to 
create a favourable atmosphere at the talks, the Foreign 
Ministry spokesman noted. 
  Participants in the Moscow round of Tajik talks agreed to 
refrain from hasty and comments. Only well-considered official 
reports will be provided to newsmen. Relations with the press 
will be coordinated by Piris-Ballon [name as received], the U.N. 
secretary general's special envoy for peace settlement in 
Tajikistan, Karasin told reporters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

