<H3> <TI>   Finance Problems Force Russian TV To Cut Broadcasts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Problems Force Russian TV To Cut Broadcasts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404163794 Moscow RIA in English 1718 GMT 1 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0404163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 1, RIA -- From April 1 considerable 
changes will be made in the principles used in drawing up weekly 
schedules of Russia Television programmes. 
  Due to financial difficulties the length of broadcasting 
will 
be cut back by 2.5 hours daily -- at the expense of repeating 
feature films and political programmes in the daytime. 
  The children's "Holiday Every Day" evening fairy-tale is 
moved from 19.45 to 18.40. 
  Theatre programmes that appeared on Saturdays at 18.15 are 
to 
be shown on Tuesdays at 21.25. 

</TEXT>

