<H3> <TI>   Czech Premier Klaus Arrives in Moscow for Working Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Premier Klaus Arrives in Moscow for Working Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0404135694 Prague CTK in English 1324 GMT 4 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0404135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 4 (CTK) -- Czech Premier Vaclav Klaus 
arrived for a two-day working visit this afternoon. 
  Klaus will meet Russian President Boris Yeltsin on Tuesday 
[5 
April] and also will hold talks with Premier Viktor 
Chernomyrdin. An agreement on support and protection of 
investments is expected to be signed during his visit. 
  Klaus will discuss the payment of Russian debt which amounts 
to some 3 billion USD [U.S. dollars]. 
  After his arrival in Moscow Premier Vaclav Klaus stated 
that he wanted "to try to resolve some issues we have not able 
to settle at lower level." 
  The Russian debt to the Czech Republic is among the issues, 
he added. 
  He said he arrived with some proposals regarding the Russian 
debt. Klaus is to meet President Boris Yeltsin and Premier 
Viktor Chernomyrdin during his two-day visit. 
  Russian media have speculated that Klaus would attempt to 
achieve a more accommodating approach by Russia to the Soviet, 
currently Russian, debt which amounts to 3 billion USD at the 
governmental level and 380 million USD with respect to the 
companies. 
  Before Klaus's visit started Prague and Moscow made it clear 
that a part of the claim could be satisfied by imports of 
Russian goods. Czech representatives have indicated they are 
interested in petrol. 
  A preliminary agreement on export of seven million tons of 
petrol and 6.9 billion cubic metres of gas was signed by the 
relevant ministries last week. However, it is not yet clear 
whether the document will be signed during Klaus's stay. 

</TEXT>

