<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Russia International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus Views Outcome of Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Klaus Views Outcome of Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0504182094 Prague CTK in English 1621 GMT 5 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0504182094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 5 (CTK) -- Premier Vaclav Klaus said 
a positive result of his two-day working visit was agreement 
with his Russian partner on a definitive solution to the 
question of the Russian debt to the Czech Republic. 
  He also voiced his satisfaction with Russia's willingness to 
conclude long-term agreements on supplies of Russian oil and gas. 
  Klaus stressed that Czech-Russian relations could not be 
limited only to the past, regarding the debt, but it was 
necessary to deal with present and future in which the imports 
of gas and petrol were of great importance for the Czech 
Republic. Russia agreed in general with preparing long-term 
agreements on both raw materials, Klaus reported. 
  Klaus welcomed that he had agreed with Russian Premier 
Viktor 
Chernomyrdin on May 30 as the binding, final date by which the 
agreement on the schedule and form of payments of the Russian 
debt would be signed. 
  Klaus admitted that Russia offered to repay a part of its 
debt by means of exports of military equipment. He stressed 
that the Czech Republic was not interested in the purchase of 
new Russian weapons, while only import of spare parts to the 
present military equipment was feasible. 
  "I found the political and economic situation (in Russia) 
was 
a bit more stable than anticipated," noted Klaus. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

