<H3> <TI>   Committee To Assist Demarcation of Border With China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee To Assist Demarcation of Border With China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604083994 Moscow RIA in English 0748 GMT 6 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0604083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khabarovsk, April 6, RIA -- A public committee to 
assist the demarcation of the Russian-Chinese border on the Amur 
and Ussuri Rivers has been established in Khabarovsk territory. 
"We have been forced to establish such an organisation to 
counter the attempts by other states to tear away Russian Far 
Eastern lands," learned Secretary of the Amur Geographic Society 
Valeriy Simakov told a RIA correspondent. "In particular we are 
concerned by the fact of the publication of an atlas of China's 
Heilungkiang Province where as Chinese territories are marked 
the Bolshoy Ussuriyskiy and Tarabarovy Islands, and also by 
their not being included in the plan of demarcation of the 
border." 
  Among the committee members are leading public and political 
figures of the territory, including geographers and historians. 

</TEXT>

