<H3> <TI>   Kazimirov Makes Proposal on Resolving Conflict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazimirov Makes Proposal on Resolving Conflict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0204151594 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0928 GMT 2 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> NC0204151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("Azg" daily), 04/02/94 -- Yesterday the 
delegation of CIS interparliamentary assembly, headed by the 
Chairman of the Kyrgyz parliament M. Sherimkulov, arrived to 
Yerevan and met the RA [Republic of Armenia] President Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan and the Chairman of the RA Supreme Council Babken 
Ararktsyan. The Special Envoy of the Russian President Vladimir 
Kazimirov, who is also a member of the delegation, yesterday 
informed us that a new revised version of the initiative on 
resolving the conflict was presented to the sides. According to 
the new project, the sides should establish a cease fire in the 
first stage, they should take the troops apart next, and than 
develop mechanisms for preventing further resumption of military 
operations. The next stage of the project plans to withdraw the 
military equipment and troops from the occupied territories, 
lifting the transportation and communications blockade, return 
of refugees. Observers are planned to be placed in the conflict 
zone when all the mentioned is implemented. 
  The delegation visited Baku on the previous day, and was 
going to leave for Stepanakert this morning. 

</TEXT>

