<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk, Polish Defense Minister Meet in Kiev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk, Polish Defense Minister Meet in Kiev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704225994 Warsaw PAP in English 1956 GMT 7 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0704225994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, April 7 -- Polish Defence Minister Piotr 
Kolodziejczyk was received by President of Ukraine Leonid 
Kravchuk on Thursday, the second day of his visit to Kiev. 
  During the meeting, the two discussed political problems in 
Europe. Both sides stressed the importance of friendly contacts 
between Poland and Ukraine. 
  Earlier in the day, Minister Kolodziejczyk and Deputy Prime 
Minister Valeriy Shmarov agreed that the setting up of a joint 
Polish-Ukrainian bank would make cooperation between the two 
Defence Ministries easier. 
  The two also discussed U.N. peacekeeping missions and the 
"Partnership for Peace" initiative. The Polish side was 
informed that Ukraine is to send more of its soldiers in blue 
helmets to former Yugoslavia in the near future. 
  Ukraine, it was stressed during the meeting, does not intend 
to join any military bloc and thus treats "Partnership for 
Peace" initiative as a factor increasing security in Europe 
allowing for broader cooperation outside military alliances. 
  A group of Polish experts meeting with Ukrainian 
counterparts 
worked on details of technical cooperation. The Polish side is 
interested in missiles while the Ukrainians in small arms. They 
also discussed the possibility of establishing communication 
links between Polish and Ukrainian General Staffs. 

</TEXT>

