<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bishkek Awaiting Early Upsurge of Economic Activity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bishkek Awaiting Early Upsurge of Economic Activity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704133394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1048 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Presidential spokesman Imankadyr Rysaliyev in a 
statement in Bishkek on Thursday has praised the pace of 
Kyrgystan's [Kyrgyzstan's] economic reforms. 
  He said the rate of inflation in March ran at 5 percent. Low 
inflation and stable currency, he said, are setting conditions 
for economic growth. 
  The statement says if the policy of economic reforms and 
financial austerity is maintained "for the next six months at 
least," good incentives will be created for the inflow of 
foreign investment and Kyrgyzstan is justified in expecting an 
upsurge of economic activity soon. Rysaliyev believes "now is 
the time to think of how to sell what is produced and to avert 
any possible glut in the domestic market." 

</TEXT>

