<HT>    "drsov068_p_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-068 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Expert on `New Ordeals' Facing Country </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Expert on `New Ordeals' Facing Country </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704192694 Yerevan SNARK in English 1106 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] Russia will face new 
ordeals in forthcoming months, announced the Russian president 
adviser and politologist Andranik Migranyan, appearing at a 
meeting with professorial staff of the Yerevan University. As 
reports the "HAYASTAN" newspaper today, Migranyan has grounded 
such a perspective on a fact that Russia experiences now an 
economic instability, so that important and cardinal decisions 
are expected in the nearest two months to lead the country out 
of crisis. He told that emergency measures introduction in 
economy and industry is being discussed already for some time in 
the government circles. 
  Migranyan estimated as nearly 40 percent the democrats' 
votes 
in Russian Duma, while there is no yet unity among the rights, 
he said. The politologist negatively characterized the 
Nazarbayev's idea of Eurasian Union, calling this initiative a 
"political bluff". 
  Speaking of the Karabakh problem, Migranyan expressed an 
opinion that the consistent policy of Russia will ultimately 
result in a settlement of conflict. However to reach this 
objective the involved parties shall not assume delirious ideas 
as their starting point, but show instead the readiness for 
compromise. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

