<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Observers Shelled by Georgian Artillery </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Observers Shelled by Georgian Artillery </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704215194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1359 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A mission of UN military observers in Abkhazia was 
shelled on April 6 by artillery of Georgian units stationed in 
the upper reaches of the Kodor River, a spokesman for the 
Abkhazian Defense Ministry said Thursday. The mission was 
shelled when it visited the villages of Lata in the Kodori 
canyon. No casualties have been reported. 
  Abkhazian Defense Minister Sultan Sosnaliyev described the 
incident as the flagrant violation by the Georgian side of the 
documents for a settlement in Abkhazia signed in Moscow recently. 
  There are wounded among the servicemen of the Abkhazian army 
and the civilian population. 

</TEXT>

