<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Refugees To Return to Abkhazia in `Two Months' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Refugees To Return to Abkhazia in `Two Months' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704190994 Yerevan SNARK in English 1230 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, April 7 (SNARK)--No less than two months 
will be necessary to organize the return of refugees to 
Abkhazia, told today in his interview to SNARK the chairman of 
Georgian Human Rights and International Relations Committee 
Aleksandr Kavsadze. He told that tomorrow, April 8, the 
four-lateral committee will sit to discuss the specific aspects 
of expected peoples' return to their homes. Kavkadze observed 
that the process will have a step-by-step character. 
  Meanwhile, told the committee chairman, the principles of 
peacekeepers' dislocation in the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict 
zone will be considered on April 12 in Geneva. Georgian side 
suggests the forces to be disposed on the whole territory of 
Abkhazia, while the Abkhazian side insists on their presence 
only along the Inguri River, known to separate the fighters, 
said Kavsadze. 

</TEXT>

