<H3> <TI>   Border Troops To Receive Aid From International Body </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Troops To Receive Aid From International Body </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0704191294 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1715 
GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0704191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of the International Immigration 
Organization, which is on a visit to our Republic, has visited 
the Border Troops General Department within the Cabinet of 
Ministers. In the course of negotiations, the two sides 
discussed the issue of granting technical assistance, as well as 
help in training Border Troops soldiers. It was agreed that the 
organization's experts, who are to arrive as early as May, will 
examine the state of affairs within the Belarusian Border Troops 
and determine the amount of aid needed. 

</TEXT>

