<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hryb Favors Economic Reunification With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hryb Favors Economic Reunification With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704201894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1824 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified BELINFORM correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk 7 April, TASS -- Belarusian Parliament Speaker 
Mechyslaw Hryb called for restoration of full-fledged economic 
ties with Russia as a way of pulling the former Soviet Republic 
out of the global crisis, of halting output decline and curbing 
inflation. 
  Addressing on Thursday a meeting in Vitebsk with regional 
law-enforcement officers, the parliament chairman came out in 
favour of rebuilding a single industrial, energy, market and 
trade space with Russia, as well as of a single monetary system 
based on the Russian rouble. Hryb noted that Russia was the 
main supplier of energy resources and of a great variety of 
component parts for the Belarusian economy. 
  When asked whether there was any alternative to a treaty 
with 
Russia, the speaker said: "First, we could agree to lift all 
customs barriers and duties, and then go ahead with further 
moves, bearing in mind that both economic and political 
sovereignty of the Belarusian state should be kept intact. This 
means that the Belarusian budget should by no means merge with 
that of Russia, nor the Republic's national bank can be 
absorbed," Hryb stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

