<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ambassador Presents Credentials to UK's Queen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassador Presents Credentials to UK's Queen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0704140194 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 6 Apr 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> PM0704140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Pavel Bogomolov: "Baku Envoy on </F>
the Thames"] 
  [Text] London, 5 Apr -- Makhmud Mamed Guliyev, Azerbaijan 
ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary to Britain, has 
presented his credentials to Queen Elizabeth II. The process of 
establishing bilateral diplomatic relations has thus officially 
been completed. Following the embassies of the Russian 
Federation, Ukraine, and Armenia, the embassy of the Caspian 
state becomes the latest full-scale diplomatic mission of the 
CIS countries on the banks of the Thames. 
  Baku is now linked by a weekly direct flight by the 
Azerbaijan Airways company with London's Gatwick Airport. This 
helps to activate bilateral business relations within whose 
framework mutually advantageous agreements and contacts have 
recently been signed between Transcaucasus enterprises, 
associations, and firms, and well known companies like "Kayzer 
[name as transliterated] Engineers," "Morrison Construction," 
"British Telecom," "Datacom," and "GPT." Talks are continuing 
on the forthcoming conclusion of a "deal of the century" aimed 
at the participation of a consortium of Western oil giants in 
the development and export of the Caspian's fuel and energy 
resources. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

