<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Deems Relations With Russia `Priority' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Deems Relations With Russia `Priority' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0704163294 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0704163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the opinion of Ukrainian Foreign Minister 
Anatoliy Zlenko, relations with Russia are a priority in our 
foreign policy. In an interview with UKRINFORM, the foreign 
minister emphasized that [word indistinct] relations between 
Ukraine and Russia serve not only the interests of our two 
countries, but also Europe in general. The minister also stated 
that the process of fulfilling the tripartite agreements of the 
Ukrainian, U.S., and Russian presidents on our nonnuclear status 
and guarantees for us has already begun. He emphasized, however, 
that all the sides must adhere to their commitments, which will 
ensure fulfillment of the agreements. 

