<H3> <TI>   Nationalists Seek Ouster of Russians From Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nationalists Seek Ouster of Russians From Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704180194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1601 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 7 April, TASS -- The commanders of nine units 
of the Black Sea Fleet have lately received letters signed by 
leaders of the Organisation of Ukrainian Nationalists who 
threatened them with physical reprisals, the Black Sea Fleet 
press centre said. 
  The press centre described the letters as a form of 
psychological pressure on the Black Sea Fleet Command. 
  Commanders of a training unit of one of the fleet bases were 
warned that "in the event of combat activities or hostilities" 
their unit will be subject to "extermination by sabotage and 
fire." Other letters demand that Russian servicemen leave 
Ukraine under threat of physical revenge. 
  The letters correctly name the numbers of all military units 
and their phone numbers. 

</TEXT>

