<H3> <TI>   Snegur Singles Out New Government's Priorities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Snegur Singles Out New Government's Priorities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704210394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1853 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The new Moldovan Government at its first meeting in 
Kishinev [Chisinau] on Thursday ruled to recommend to the 
parliament to ratify the agreement on Moldova's entry the CIS 
and the Economic Union in the near future. 
  Speaking at the meeting, Moldovan President Mircea Snegur 
singled out the main aspects of the Cabinet's activities. 
  "It is not enough for the government to receive certain 
powers from the parliament -- it should be effective, 
functional, take decisions in time, offering draft laws and 
necessary mechanisms and implementing them," the president said. 
  Snegur noted that the re-organization of ministries and 
departments should be carried out "quickly and with a 
considerable reduction of their personnel." 
  Snegur said that another priority is the preparation of a 
Cabinet program for the next two-three years. He said that it 
could be outlined by July 1 and should envisage the acceleration 
of the restructuring and modernization of the national economy, 
privatization and social support of the population. 

</TEXT>

