<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drafting of Concept for Protecting CIS Borders Begins </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Drafting of Concept for Protecting CIS Borders Begins </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0704124494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1200 
GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0704124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report attributed to RIA] </F>
  [Text] For the first time within the CIS framework, the 
drafting of a general concept has started, providing for the 
protection of the external borders of the CIS using the means 
and resources of the entire commonwealth. This has been told to 
an RIA correspondent by General Colonel Andrey Nikolayev, 
Russian Federation Border Troops commander in chief. According 
to him, the concept envisions a system of mutual commitments of 
the [CIS] states in providing security of both their own 
national borders and the borders of other countries. Protection 
of the borders will be maintained in a coordinated manner. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

