<H3> <TI>   Russian Delegation Head Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Delegation Head Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0804102394 Tallinn ETA in English 0728 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0804102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From 8 April HOMMIKULEHT, p 3; "News Bulletin" No. 67] </F>
  [Text] The future of the Estonian-Russian negotiations is 
vague, head of the Russian delegation Vasily Svirin told the ETA 
yesterday. The 18th round made progress only in some issues 
concerning citizenship, while the problem of the retired 
military remained unsolved, he said. The Estonian side had 
rejected all Russian proposals, Svirin explained. He added that 
the Russian side proposes a complex solution of the Paldiski 
issue, while the Estonian proposals had only concerned the 
removal of the nuclear fuel. The Russian side is ready to 
initial the agreement on Paldiski, Svirin announced. 

</TEXT>

