<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Emergency Decree on N. Ossetia Approved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Emergency Decree on N. Ossetia Approved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704120694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1131 
GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lyudmila Yermakova, ITAR-TASS parliamentary </F>
correspondent] 
  [Text] Moscow, 7 April -- The Russian president's decree, 
"On introducing a state of emergency in parts of the Republic of 
North Ossetia and the Ingush Republic," which extends the state 
of emergency for two more months, was approved by the Federation 
Council today. 
  The situation in the zone of conflict was discussed behind 
closed doors for four hours, however, the issue remained open 
and the problem will be further discussed tomorrow. Vasiliy 
Tarasenko, chairman of the committee for federation affairs and 
regional policy, told an ITAR-TASS correspondent that attempts 
had been made to block the approval of the decree on various 
pretexts. In his view, "It is not as much a result of the 
conflict between the two republics as a way to influence 
relations between power structures in general." Unfortunately, 
"Politics and the stirring up of the conflict at the expense of 
people's sufferings interfere" in the problem of approving the 
presidential decree, he remarked. 

</TEXT>

