<H3> <TI>   National Guard Military Council Discusses Duties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Guard Military Council Discusses Duties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0704141494 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1100 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0704141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian National Guard [NHU] performs its 
duties, as established by law, regarding the protection of our 
constitutional system, the state's territorial integrity, the 
lives and personal dignity of citizens, and their rights and 
freedoms against criminal encroachment. This was the topic 
discussed at today's meeting of the Ukrainian National Guard 
Military Council, which also addressed ways of improving combat 
training, education, discipline, and solidarity among units and 
formations. Guards Major General Mykola Melnyk, the NHU deputy 
commander, delivered a report. The meeting was chaired by Guards 
Lieutenant General Volodymyr Kukharuk, the NHU commander in 
chief. 

</TEXT>

