<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Spokesman's Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Spokesman's Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704170294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1555 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow April 7 ITAR-TASS -- The press secretary of 
the president of the Russian Federation, Vyacheslav Kostikov 
issued a statement today, which says: 
  "Emotions prevailed over politics in the course of 
discussion 
of the question about the procurator-general in the Federation 
Council. This is characteristic of Russia's fresh state 
institutions. "But real facts exist apart from emotions. 
  "It is a reality that Aleksey I. Kazannik tendered his 
resignation of his own free will. 
  "It is a reality that the president accepted his resignation 
and named a new candidate for the post. 
  "These realities cannot be ignored. 
  "Hence, it is necessary to look for a way out of the 
situation. 
  "A situation of vacuum or double power cannot be allowed to 
emerge in the sphere of prosecutorship. This blocks the entire 
system of prosecuting activity at a time when the country is 
engulfed by a wave of crime. It will be difficult to make clear 
to the people why an impasse appeared in which the Federation 
Council has found itself. The prestige of this body can suffer 
as a result. 
  "The Federation Council cannot be permitted to become the 
initiator of political braking at a moment when Russia has begun 
its movement toward concord. 
  "One would like to believe that the Federation Council will 
act proceeding primarily from the supreme interests of the 
state. The possibilities for this are far from exhaustion." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

