<DOCNO> FBIS4-15385 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov068_b_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-068 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko: Kazannik Resigned Without Pressure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shumeyko: Kazannik Resigned Without Pressure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804125294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1111 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 TASS -- Former Russian prosecutor 
general Aleksey Kazannik confirmed his resignation on Friday on 
his own will and no pressure was exerted on him, according to 
speaker of the Federation Council Vladimir Shumeyko. 
  "Kazannik adopted the decision on his own initiative", he 
told TASS adding that the former prosecutor asked to be given 
the floor for his statement why [as received] talking to a group 
of deputies. 
  "The essence of his speech was important to me and I 
realised 
that regardless of political colours the essence was correct and 
aimed at achieving civic peace in society", Shumeyko said. "That 
is why we have agreed to give the floor to Kazannik", he added. 
  Shumeyko believes that in a couple of weeks the upper 
chamber 
will return to the issue of the prosecutor general. It will 
accept Kazannik's resignation and will consider the new 
candidate nominated by the president - Aleksey Ilyushenko. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

