<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov To Chair </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov To Chair </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804100694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0802 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 8 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin has signed an edict on the Russian Federation's 
presidential expert analysis service. The Expert Analysis 
Council and the Analysis Center attached to the Russian 
Federation president as well as the Information Technology 
Center for Analytical Research within the presidential 
administration are being set up in order to improve provision of 
analytical and information services for the Russian Federation 
president. 
  Members of the Expert Analysis Council will be working on 
voluntary basis. Sergey Filatov will act as its chairman. 
Yevgeniy Yasin is appointed head of the Analytical Center and 
Marat Guriyev head of the Information Technology Cente for 
Analytical Research. 
  The press service of the Russian president reports that the 
General Policy Analysis Center and the Socioeconomic Policy 
Analysis Center within the Russian Federation presidential 
administration have been abolished. 
  The edict establishes provisions for the Expert Analysis 
Council and the Analysis Center attached to the president of the 
Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

