<H3> <TI>   Shakhray Comments on New Post, Duties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shakhray Comments on New Post, Duties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704204994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1715 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vice-Premier, Minister for Nationalities and 
Regional Policy of the Russian Federation Sergey Shakhray 
expressed the opinion that he will be in charge of national and 
regional policy in the government, as well as relations with the 
Federal Assembly and the media. He gave an interview to 
INTERFAX after the president issued a decree nominating Shakhray 
the deputy prime minister. Shakhray noted that a final decision 
on the range of his duties will be taken at a meeting of the 
government presidium. 
  Shakhray said that after the new appointment he has no 
intention of losing his deputy mandate. He pointed out that he 
is not working in the ruling structures in the State Duma. "My 
job in the lower chamber of the parliament boils down to 
coordination of activities of the Russian Unity and Accord 
Party's faction," he noted. 

</TEXT>

