<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sulakshin To `Defect' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sulakshin To `Defect' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804140394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1045 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Member of the Russia's Choice (RC) faction in the 
State Duma, Stepan Sulakshin, says he intends to defect to the 
unregistered parliamentary group known as the December 12 Union. 
To be registered, the group must win over six people. 
  In an interview with Interfax, the group's co-chairman 
Yevgeniy Bushmin said two more members of RC -- Rashid 
Ismaghilov and Vladimir Yuzhakov -- are negotiating to switch 
over as well. And, according to Bushmin, one or two members of 
the New Regional Politics group could be expected to join the 
"Decembrists" ranks. Bushmin refused to identify these. 
  Another leader of the December 12 Union group, Irina 
Khakamada, told Interfax she was dissatisfied with the RC's 
decision to show understanding if some of its members sided with 
the Decemebr 12 Union group. In Khakamada's view, the RC could 
have moved to help Decenber 12 devotees by campaigning for their 
official recognition and rights as a group in parliament. 
  On Friday Gennadiy Burbulis also announced his decision to 
leave the Russia's Choice group. 

</TEXT>

