<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Choice, December 12 Union To Cooperate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Choice, December 12 Union To Cooperate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704210994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1853 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Russia's Choice parliamentary group approved at 
its Thursday meeting the proposal made by Boris Fedorov, the 
leader of the unregistered group December 12 Union, that the two 
groups start closer cooperation on most important issues on the 
agenda of the lower house. 
  Russia's Choice leader Yegor Gaydar also told his supporters 
that the December 12 Union was short of members to be registered 
officially. It had 29 while 35 were needed for official 
registration. The Russia's Choice adopted a decision saying 
that it would not punish its members who voluntarily join the 
December 12 Union. 
  Gleb Yakunin called for a closer bloc between the two 
groups. 
Gaydar supported the idea and said that he would help the 
setting up of a club of democratic deputies. Gaydar also said 
that he had called on Grigoriy Yavlinskiy, leader of another 
pro-democracy faction, to work closer together and that Fedorov 
had done the same. 

</TEXT>

