<H3> <TI>   New Financial-Industrial Group Approved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Financial-Industrial Group Approved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0704142194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Apr 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM0704142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Aleksandr Golyayev report: "`Sokol' in Flight"] </F>
  [Text] The Interdepartmental Comission for Promoting the 
Organization of Industrial Companies and Financial-Industrial 
Groups has approved the project for the "Sokol" 
Financial-Industrial Group, which has been submitted to it, and 
adopted a decision to register it and issue its certificate of 
registration. The project was elaborated on the intiative of 
specialists and leaders from a number of major industrial and 
financial enterprises of the Central Chernozem Zone and other 
economic regions of Russia, and was backed by the 
administrations of Voronezh, Kursk, and Sverdlovsk Oblasts. 
  Projections suggest that, already in its first stage, 
"Sokol" 
will be able to secure a growth in the volume of manufactured 
output from 326 billion rubles [R] last year to R1.27 trillion 
in 1996. The recoupment period of the investment projects will 
be from two to five years. 
  "The creation of the `Sokol' Financial-Industrial Group 
meets 
the fundamental interests of federal industrial policy. This 
policy aims at developing the science and production complex, 
ensuring the competitiveness of Russian-made products, and 
raising economic potential," Igor Shurchkov, chairman of the 
State Committee for Industrial Policy, said. "We wish to use 
the experience of `Sokol' and of the `Uralskiye Zavody' 
Financial-Industrial Group which was set up earlier to prove the 
efficiency and promise of such groups." 

</TEXT>

