<H3> <TI>   Spending on Foreign Currency Increases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spending on Foreign Currency Increases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0804090794 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 7 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0804090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [RIA report: "Russians Love To Buy Hard Currency"] </F>
  [Text] The Russian population is increasing its spending 
on hard currency: 1.8253 trillion rubles [R] were spent last 
December, R1.8572 trillion in January, and... R1.8803 trillion 
in February. 
  Compared with January 1993, when Russians spent R17 billion 
on hard currency, spending has increased virtually 111-fold. 
This is indicated in an analytical article prepared by the 
Russian Ministry of the Economy. 

</TEXT>

