<F P=106> [RIA report: "Russian AES's Plan To Increase Power </F>
Generation" -- from page I of FINANSOVYYE IZVESTIYA section] 
  [Text] According to Russian Atomic Energy Minister Viktor 
Mikhaylov, by the year 2010 it is planned to increase the amount 
of power generated at Russia's AES's [nuclear electric power 
stations] by a factor of 1.5. The country's AES's currently 
generate 22,000 megawatts, around 12 percent of all the power 
produced in the country. The proportion of atomic energy is 
expected to rise over the next 15 years to 20 percent. In the 
near future the Ministry of Atomic Energy plans to bring on 
stream the Kalinin, Kursk, and Novovoronezh AES's. 

