<H3> <TI>   Grachev on Minimal Number of Recruits Needed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev on Minimal Number of Recruits Needed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804143294 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1230 GMT 8 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev has said that 
only about 180,000 people can realistically be conscripted into 
the armed forces in spring 1994. Speaking at the Defense 
Collegium in Moscow, he said that for the country's defense 
capability to be maintained, a minimum of 700,000 new recruits 
should be inducted into the army and navy. Grachev said the 
clause in the law on defense that says the number of people in 
the armed forces is restricted to one percent of the population 
of Russia should be changed. A million and a half is not an 
army but a military formation capable of undertaking local 
combat activity, the minister believes. 

</TEXT>

