<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ulmanis Derides Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ulmanis Derides Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0704151494 Riga LETA in English 1423 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0704151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga LETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Statement by the President of the Republic of Latvia </F>
Guntis Ulmanis"] 
  [Text] On April 6 of this year, I received an ITAR-TASS 
report that Russian President Boris Yeltsin has agreed to a 
Russian Ministry of Defence proposal to establish Russian 
military bases on Latvian territory. The report states that the 
Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, together with the Russian 
Ministry of Defence and other ministries, is to begin 
negotiations on this issue and to draft the appropriate 
agreements. 
  The obviously contradicts the agreements initialed by the 
government delegations of both states, and raised doubts about 
the true intentions of the Russian Government delegation in the 
process of drafting the agreements. This statement caused 
justified concern for the planned meeting between the presidents 
of Latvian and Russia and the development of potential political 
dialogue. It does not assure domestic and foreign political 
stability, and diminishes trust in Russia as a partner state in 
agreements. The building of Russian military bases on Latvian 
territory would be a real threat to Latvian sovereignty and 
security and would destabilize not only the Baltic region, but 
also Western Europe. 
  Over the last few hours, I have repeatedly attempted to 
contact the commander-in-chief of the Russian North-West 
Military Group General Mayorov and President Yeltsin's 
administration in order to obtain an explanation. As yet, I 
have not received an answer, which points to deliberate evasion 
from providing an explanation. 
  Latvia will never allow the building of a Russian military 
base on its territory. 
  [Signed] Guntis Ulmanis, president of the Republic of 
Latvia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

