<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Faction Leader Wants Yeltsin Denial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Faction Leader Wants Yeltsin Denial </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0704181294 Tallinn BNS in English 1648 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0704181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Apr 07, BNS -- The decision of President 
Boris Yeltsin to set up military bases in Latvia would change 
the political situation, said Indulis Berzins, of the Latvia's 
Way faction. 
  The motion would also and endanger the implementation of 
U.N. 
General Assembly's resolution on the complete and immediate 
withdrawal of Russian troops from the Baltic states, he said. 
  Certain ruling political forces in Russia dislike the 
anticipated agreement with Latvia because they hope to make an 
advantage of the present situation when there is no formal 
agreement to keep Russian troops in Latvia, Berzins said. 
  Latvia, however, should not sign the initialed agreements on 
troop withdrawal before additional talks between authorized 
state delegations, Berzins added. 
  Berzins claims that the information about "the technical 
mistake" in the text of Yeltsin's resolution "does not and will 
not enhance confidence" unless the Russian president himself 
issues an official statement. 

</TEXT>

