<H3> <TI>   Former Minister To Head Local Election Alliance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former Minister To Head Local Election Alliance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0804101894 Tallinn BNS in English 0712 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0804101894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] RIGA, Apr 06, BNS - The Saimnieks (Master) 
political association was created to participate in the coming 
local governments elections, said Ziedonis Cevers, ex-interior 
minister and president of the Drosiba (Security) foundation. 
  Saimnieks will nominate practical specialists who have 
proved 
their abilities in various spheres of life, Cevers told 
reporters. 
  Cevers himself plans to run for Riga mayor. 
  BNS asked Cevers to name the priorities of Saimnieks' 
economic program but he answered that the association was 
established only recently and its programs are not ready yet. 
  Another leader of the new organization, President of the 
Private Enterprise Association Valdis Krisbergs, told BNS that 
the emphasis should be put on small and medium size business 
development and welfare of people. Krisbergs characterized the 
Latvian capital, Riga, as "the poorest and the most expensive 
city in the world." 
  Other founders of Saimnieks are MPs Eriks Kaza, Ernests 
Jurkans, actor Ivars Kalnins. 

</TEXT>

