<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Landsbergis Derides Alleged Plan for Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Landsbergis Derides Alleged Plan for Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0704181194 Tallinn BNS in English 1648 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0704181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Apr 07, BNS -- Vytautas Landsbergis, 
leader of the Lithuanian parliament's rightist opposition, 
claimed Russia's plans to create military bases in Latvia are "a 
political aggression resembling Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's (Russian 
ultranationalist) statements." 
  Commenting on the Russian president's recent decree, 
Landsbergis said "Russia's intention to create military bases in 
neighboring countries is a new imperialistic defiance of the 
international community and civilized norms accepted in it," 
Landsbergis said in a statement circulated Thursday [7 April]. 
  The opposition leader expressed regret that the Russian 
president has to assent to demands of the military. "Latvia's 
ascription to a group of states where Russia acts as if at home 
is very dangerous to the international law." 

</TEXT>

