<H3> <TI>   Kostikov Explains Mistake on Skrunda Radar Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kostikov Explains Mistake on Skrunda Radar Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804150294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1412 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 TASS -- Press Secretary of the 
Russian president Vyacheslav Kostikov explained the technical 
mistake in the document that allegedly makes possible the 
deployment of a military base in Latvia with a language 
confusion. 
  Kostikov told a briefing here today that the military 
sometimes call a base an object. Thus, the Skrunda Radar 
Station was named a base by mistake instead of an object. 
  "None has planned to build a military base, and the Latvian 
leadership was presented apologies in connection with the 
technical mistake," he said. 
  As for military bases in Commonwealth States, the Russian 
military presence there is intiated by the Commonwealth States 
themselves, stressed the presidential press secretary. 

</TEXT>

