<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris </F>
Krivoshey and Vladimir Taranov] 
  [Text] Moscow 7 April, TASS -- Russia welcomes strict 
observance of the cease-fire agreement signed in Zagreb on 29 
March by delegations of the Republic of Croatia and Serbs living 
on territories under U.N. control, spokesman for the Russian 
Foreign Ministry Grigoriy Karasin told a briefing on Thursday. 
  The fact that the warring factions are precisely following 
the schedule of troop withdrawal to new disengagement lines, set 
by the cease-fire agreement, makes it possible to hope that both 
sides will fulfill their commitments in full and on time, the 
Russian diplomat noted. 

