<H3> <TI>   Yugoslav Assembly Delegation Arrives in Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yugoslav Assembly Delegation Arrives in Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704182494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1501 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 7 Apr (TANJUG) -- A Yugoslav Assembly 
delegation led by Radoman Bozovic, the president of the Chamber 
of Citizens, arrived in Moscow this afternoon at the invitation 
of Ivan Rybkin, the president of the Russian parliaments's lower 
house. The delegation is to have talks at the Russian 
parliament with Ivan Rybkin, with leaders of some parties, and 
other Russian officials. 
  Parliamentarian and other forms of cooperation will be 
discussed during the talks, as well as the situation in the 
former Yugoslavia and ways of resolving it. It is expected that 
initiatives announced by the Russian parliament in connection 
with the lifting of sanctions against Yugoslavia will also be 
discussed. 
  This is the first visit by a Yugoslav parliamentary 
delegation since the sanctions were introduced. 

</TEXT>

