<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Ends Talks in Sweden; Returns to Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Ends Talks in Sweden; Returns to Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704205994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1956 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Vlasov] </F>
  [Text] Pskov 7 April, TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev met on Thursday with his Swedish counterpart 
Margaretha af Ugglas in the town of Pskov to consider 
possiblities of revitalizing the economy of Russia's 
northwestern region. 
  The Pskov region attracted the attention of Swedish 
businessmen by its rich natural resources and developed 
industry. They also hope to benefit considerably by taking part 
in rehabilitation of the region's ailing agrarian sector. 
  After discussing ways of improving the Pskov region's 
economy 
by joint efforts and seeing the sights of the old Russian town, 
Mrs. af Ugglas left for Sweden. 
  Meanwhile, her Russian counterpart visited the Pechora 
segment of the Russian-Estonian border, where he was informed 
about the construction of border facilities and about the 
current situation on the border which has been deteriorating 
with every passing day. 
  Senior officials of the regional administration told the 
Russian foreign minister that they would like to improve ties 
with the Baltic republics rather than to tighten a border 
regime. Nevertheless, Kozyrev said, it would be better to 
reinforce the border with technical means than with bodies of 
Russian soldiers. 
  On Thursday night, the Russian foreign minister flew off 
back 
to Moscow. 

</TEXT>

