<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns `Terrorist Act' in 'Afula </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Condemns `Terrorist Act' in 'Afula </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704190794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1715 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "With deep bitterness and indignation," Moscow 
received the reports on the attack on Israeli citizens in the 
city of 'Afula. "We harshly condemn this terrorist act, which 
led to human victims and express our condolences to the families 
of those killed," the head of the information and press 
department of the Russian Foreign Ministry, Grigory Karasin, 
told a briefing in Moscow Thursday. 
  Karasin said "the event again raises the need to immediately 
carry out the measures to ensure the safety of Palestinian 
civilians in the occupied territories agreed on at the 
Palestinian-Israeli talks." 
  "Russia proceeds from the fact that this terrorist act 
should 
not distract Palestinians and Israelis from their main goal, 
this being to continue negotiations on the temporary 
introduction of Palestinian self-government on the occupied 
territories in accordance with the Declaration of Principles," 
Karasin was quoted as saying. "Once again, we call on both 
sides to show the maximum restraint, self-control and political 
will to achieve mutually acceptable agreements within the 
framework of the Middle East peace process." 

</TEXT>

