<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Policy Change After Hosokawa's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Policy Change After Hosokawa's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804103594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0837 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Solntsev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 ITAR-TASS -- The resignation of the 
Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa is Japan's internal 
affair. The Moscow policy of developing comprehensive relations 
with Japan remains unchanged, a ranking official of the Russian 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs told ITAR-TASS today. 
  He stressed that these relations will continue to develop on 
the basis of the Tokyo declaration signed after the 
Russo-Japanese summit last October. 
  The Tokyo declaration outlined the strategic perspective for 
the development of all-round ties between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

