<F P=101> Russia National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Physician Says Yeltsin `In Best of Health' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Physician Says Yeltsin `In Best of Health' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504175494 Moscow RIA in English 1556 GMT 5 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0504175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 5, RIA -- "Yeltsin was his old self 
again," said Dr. Bella Denisenko, head of the parliamentary 
health committee, after he received spokesmen of Russia's Choice 
parliamentary group yesterday. "He was eager to cooperate with 
all reformers, especially Russia's Choice Party, currently in 
the making [as received] on our group's basis." 
  Information of MPs back from their constituencies shocked 
the 
president. He heard about local election returns forged, 
statistics held back, bosses' arbitrary action, and a new ruling 
class emerging from among executive and legislative officers. 
Russia's Choice thinks the president ought to be more choosy 
with official appointments. 
  Despite all latest rumours, Dr. Denisenko found Mr. Yeltsin 
in the best of health. 

</TEXT>

