<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Stresses Efforts To Solve Tajik Conflict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Stresses Efforts To Solve Tajik Conflict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504181994 Moscow RIA in English 1734 GMT 5 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0504181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 5, RIA -- Speaking at the opening 
session of the talks between the official Tajik leaders and the 
opposition on the internal settlement, Russia's Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev said Russia regards its assistance in promoting 
the settlement of the political crisis in Tajikistan both as 
moral duty and the effort which corresponds to Russia's national 
interests. In the opinion of the top Russian diplomat, the 
talks will gradually gain significance, and called on the 
negotiators to prevent an outbreak of a new conflict in 
Tajikistan. He noted that Russia will shape its relations with 
respect to both parties proceeding from the progress of the 
talks. 

</TEXT>

