<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Adopts Program To Cut Emigration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Adopts Program To Cut Emigration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0604111194 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 5 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0604111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Attempts To Halt Emigration in </F>
Kirghizia"] 
  [Text] The Kirghiz Government has formulated a program to 
reduce the level of emigration. 
  It contains a package of documents aimed at creating the 
requisite legislative base for emigration based on international 
legal norms as well as proposals to create joint ventures and 
production units, interstate investment funds, and a balanced 
cadre policy. The package also includes documents examining the 
full-fledged use of Russian within the system of public 
education, science, technology, and culture. A considerable 
part of the program is devoted to tightening up administrative 
and criminal liability for fueling interethnic enmity. What is 
more, special measures have been formulated to avert a "brain 
drain." 

</TEXT>

