<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Rejects Stationing of `Alien Strategic Units' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Rejects Stationing of `Alien Strategic Units' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704194694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1715 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The Belarusian Government has not announced any 
official position regarding Russia's desire to set up its 
military bases in the CIS states," head of the governmental 
board of national security, Major-General Valeriy Pavlov told 
INTERFAX. 
  At the same time, he noted that "alien strategic units 
cannot 
be stationed in Belarus, because that would run contrary to 
Belarus' aspiration to neutrality and non-nuclear status." 
  In the opinion of Valeriy Pavlov, "the present of Russian 
aviation bases or air-defense units in Belarus would help 
Belarussian colleagues to maintain "good condition," to get 
familiarized with the latest examples of equipment and arms and 
to resolve social problems." 
  Valeriy Pavlov noted that "all options of the presence of 
foreign military bases in Belarus will be thoroughly studied." 

</TEXT>

