<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kazimirov Meets With Nagorno-Karabakh Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazimirov Meets With Nagorno-Karabakh Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704194294 Baku TURAN in English 1638 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (April 6) TURAN--"The aim of my visit to Baku 
remains unchanged: to work on an agreement proposal concerning 
the resolution to the conflict", said Vladimir Kazimirov, 
special representative to the Russian President on 
Nagorno-Karabakh, during his arrival to the Azerbaijani capital 
during an interview with a TURAN correspondent. 
  According to Kazimirov the peacemaking mission will attempt 
to clarify positions regarding the Russian peace plan. 
Kazimirov noted that because of poor weather he could not 
arrive in Khankendi [Stepanakert] during his past visit. "The 
short meeting with several leaders of Nagorno-Karabakh was held 
half way between Yerevan and Stepanakert, somewhere on the 
border of Azerbaijan", said Kazimirov. 
  "The peacemaking and mediation missions must be conducted 
stage by stage, neither side wants its concessions to be 
announced publicly prematurely, and there has been no concession 
from the opposite side. That is why we should not hurry," said 
Kazimirov. 
  As has been earlier announced, Kazimirov arrived in Baku a 
week ago accompanied by members of the CIS Interparliamentary 
delegation in order to introduce the peace plan prepared by 
Russia and presented to the Azeri and Armenian sides. The major 
points of the plan provide for a cease-fire, the withdrawal from 
all occupied territories and a revision of the status of 
Nagorno-Karabakh. 

</TEXT>

