<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Urges Russia To Adhere to Commitments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Urges Russia To Adhere to Commitments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704211194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2050 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Albert Maloveryan] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn April 7 TASS -- Estonian President Lennart 
Meri, State Assembly Chairman Ulo Nugis and Prime Minister Mart 
Laar signed on Thursday a statement saying: "At the 18th round 
of Russian-Estonian talks, which has just finished, the Russian 
side linked the deadline for complete withdrawal of Russian 
troops (August 31, 1994) to the conditions that had been already 
settled during previous rounds, thus casting doubt on the very 
deadline of troop withdrawal approved by the international 
community. 
  Estonia cannot agree to new terms, but is still ready to 
negotiate with Russia with a view to benevolently surmount all 
difficulties. However, the Estonian republic regards President 
Boris Yeltsin's order #174 of April 5, providing for creation of 
new military bases not only in CIS member-countries but also in 
the Latvian republic, as Russia's departure from its earlier 
commitments, as well as from international agreements and 
principles. 
  With this in view, the Estonian Foreign Ministry and 
Estonia's representatives abroad are instructed to do their 
utmost in persuading foreign leaders to recall Russia that it 
should unconditionally adhere to its international commitments 
and to pull out promptly and in the proper order its troops from 
Latvia and Estonia, which has been repeatedly called for by 
numerous international documents. 
  Unfortunately, certain political circles in Moscow are quite 
likely to use this situation to engineer provocations against 
Estonia and Latvia. But such attempts are doomed to failure. 
Estonia will resolutely counteract pressure from Russia. The 
Estonian people will go ahead with creating new values on its 
straight way back to Europe". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

