<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean President Blasts Ukraine for Interference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean President Blasts Ukraine for Interference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704170794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1547 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report By UKRINFORM correspondent Lev Ryabchikov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol 7 April, TASS -- "Kiev continues to 
prevent us from tackling the economy in earnest and pushes for 
confrontation," Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov told a news 
conference in Simferopol on Thursday. 
  Speaking about his attitude towards Ukrainian President 
Leonid Kravchuk's decision to appoint his representative in the 
Crimea, Meshkov said "this happened at the most difficult stage 
of the establishment of the Crimea's statehood, on the eve of 
the elections to the parliament." 
  "But we will do everything possible in order that elections 
go off successfully on 10 April," he added. He said that the 
Crimea has lost Valeriy Gorbatov, who has been appointed 
Kravchuk's representative in the Crimea, as its citizen. 
  Meshkov also spoke about the results of his trip to Cyprus 
where he had reached an agreement to open a Cypriot trade office 
in the Crimea. Documents to this effect will be signed during 
Cypriot leaders' visit to the Crimea. 

</TEXT>

