<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Meet Doctors During Visit to Spain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Meet Doctors During Visit to Spain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804112594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0940 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 TASS -- President Boris Yeltsin will 
see doctors in Barcelona during his upcoming visit to Spain next 
week, but it is not clear whether the president wants to undergo 
a medical check-up or just thank the doctors who had cured him 
after an air accident in 1990. 
  Presidential spokesman Vyacheslav Kosikov told reporters on 
Friday that Yeltsin will see the doctors who operated on his 
back hurt when the plane made an emergency landing. 
  "I cannot say whether it will be a consultation or a gesture 
of gratitude to them", Kostikov said. The doctors had examined 
the Russian president in Moscow last September. Kostikov said 
that in Barcelona Yeltsin also plans to visit Olympic sites. 

</TEXT>

