<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Supports Latvia on Military Bases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Supports Latvia on Military Bases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704124994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1048 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "Only the Latvian Republic can decided whose 
military bases can be stationed on its territory," says a 
message distributed by the Lithuanian Foreign Ministry on 
Wednesday evening after the publication of the Russian 
president's order on the creation of Russian military bases on 
the territories of CIS states and the Latvian Republic "to 
ensure security of the Russian Federation and the above 
mentioned states and to test new armaments and military 
equipment." 
  On April 6 a source in the Kremlin reported to Interfax that 
the wording about the creation of a military base in Latvia "is 
the result of an inappropriate phrase which was included into 
one of the documents of the Defense Ministry and then appeared 
in a corresponding order of the Russian president." 
  The message of the Lithuanian Foreign Ministry underlined 
that "unilateral actions by Russia aimed at the creation of 
military bases in the Latvian Republic despite the will of this 
sovereign state contradicts the principles of international law 
and international obligations taken by Russia as a member of the 
UN and CSCE." 

</TEXT>

