<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Says Russia To Join PFP After 20 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Says Russia To Join PFP After 20 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804164394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1528 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Andrey Serov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 TASS -- Russia is getting ready to 
sign a framework document on its participation in NATO's 
Partnership for Peace [PFP] program after April 20, Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev told member of the EC Commission 
Hans Van der Broek here today. 
  The documents are being finalized with due account of 
Russian 
peculiarities as a nuclear power. 
  The sides focused today on preparation of an agreement 
between Russia and the European Union. There are two problems 
to be solved. The first one, banks, has been settled at the 
experts' level. The other is more complicated as it concerns 
sales of nuclear fuel. Moscow is not satisfied with the quotas 
envisaged by the draft agreement. 
  The sides basically agree that it is time to finish 
preparations and sign the agreement. 

</TEXT>

