<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kostikov Suggests Linking PFP, G-7 Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kostikov Suggests Linking PFP, G-7 Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804082294 Paris AFP in English 0812 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0804082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 8 (AFP) -- Russia wants to link its 
joining the NATO Partnership for Peace [PFP] to joining the G-7 
group of industrial nations, presidency spokesman Viacheslav 
Kostikov said. 
  "If we are invited into the political and military 
partnership, it would be logical to make an approach in the 
economic sphere," he told reporters. "Russia would like to join 
the G-7. Why not link the two problems," he added. 

</TEXT>

