<H3> <TI>   General Rules out Foreign Military Presence </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General Rules out Foreign Military Presence </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004151394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1322 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1004151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Chief of the National Security Agency under the 
Belarussian [Belarusian] government Major-General Valeriy Pavlov 
told INTERFAX Minsk had not yet voiced its view of the Russian 
plans to build bases in Commonwealth republics. 
  But, Pavlov said the deployment of strategic units of a 
foreign army in Belarus was out of question as it would 
contradict the Belarussian decision to be a neutral and 
nuclear-free country. 
  In Pavlov's view, the deployment in Belarus of Russian air 
bases or antiaircraft units would keep Belarussian armymen in 
good shape. The Belarussians would familiarize with advanced 
know-how and be able to resolve their social problems. 
  According to Pavlov, Minsk would study in detail every 
scenario for the creation of foreign army bases in Belarus. 

</TEXT>

