<H3> <TI>   Referendum Proposed on Economic Integration With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Referendum Proposed on Economic Integration With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804195194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1742 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich did not 
rule out the possibility that Belarusians would be polled on 
economic integration with Russia on 23 June when the 
presidential elections are held. 
  In an exclusive INTERFAX interview in Minsk Friday Kebich 
said that he had initially proposed such a move at the meeting 
of the government presidium Tuesday, 5 April and the idea was 
supported by all cabinet members. 
  Kebich said that, according to sociological research, an 
absolute majority of Belarusian citizens supported a union with 
Russia. 
  Kebich said that Belarus was a stable country and the 
economic union treaty that had been ratified by parliament 
contributed to the stability. He thought, however, that a poll 
would indirectly enhance the long-term stability of that treaty, 
whatever the political situation in the country. 

</TEXT>

