<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Snegur, Sangheli Address First Meeting of New Cabinet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Snegur, Sangheli Address First Meeting of New Cabinet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804170894 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1907 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0804170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 7/4/1994 -- "The time of 
unfounded promises and declarations and political confrontation 
that split up the precedent governments has gone," stated today 
President Mircea Snegur during the first session of the new 
Moldovan Government. He mentioned that Moldova is in a very 
complicated situation which is decisive for the future of the 
reforms. The president insisted on the need to stop the 
economic decline, to stabilize the situation and to lay the 
foundation for the economic take-off that would lead to the 
consolidation of the statehood. Snegur emphasized that the 
reorganization of the ministries and departments [words 
indistinct] and promoted with consistency according to the 
Memorandum signed with the IMF. Referring to the activity 
program of the new Government, Premier Andrei Sangheli inferred 
weight to the social protection and in particular medical care. 
The government examined and proposed for parliamentary debates 
the draft decision on ratifying the agreement "Regarding the 
Creation of the Commonwealth of Independent States" with the 
amendments imposed by the Moldovan legislation and the treaty 
"Regarding the Creation of the Economic Union." Vice-Premier 
Valentin Cunev mentioned that amendments to the agreement have 
to do with preserving Moldova's independence, meaning that 
Moldova will not adhere to military agreements, creation of a 
joint army and ruble zone. 

</TEXT>

