<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester, Gagauz Republics Approve Accord Ratification </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester, Gagauz Republics Approve Accord Ratification </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804205394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1950 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] State Secretary of the self-proclaimed 
Transdniestrian Republic, Valeriy Litskay, was satisfied with 
the fact that the Moldovan parliament had ratified the agreement 
within the scope of the CIS and the Economic Union. He 
suggested in an interview with INTERFAX that this would help 
renew the talks between Kishinev [Chisinau] and Tiraspol at a 
completely new level. 
  The Gagauz leaders shared this opinion. They approved of the 
ratification of the agreement by the Moldovan parliament at the 
session of the Gagauz parliament in Kamrat today. 
  President of the self-proclaimed Gagauz Republic, Stepan 
Topal, said in an interview with INTERFAX on the telephone that 
the Gagauz leaders had been seeking ratification of these 
documents for the last two years. He suggested that the 
Agrarian Democratic Party and the Socialist party currently in 
power in Moldova and their moves, including the agreement's 
ratification, had laid a good foundation for the renewal of the 
Moldovan-Gagauz talks at a new level. 
  The Gagauz parliament approved the activities by the 
commission for renewal of the talks with Kishinev on the status 
of the regions with a largely Gagauz population and recommended 
that the commission work even more energetically. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

