<H3> <TI>   CSCE Mission Head Talks With President Snegur </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE Mission Head Talks With President Snegur </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804143594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1045 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Talking to the leader of the CSCE Moldovan mission 
Richard Samuel in Kishinev [Chisinau], Moldovan President Mircea 
Snegur pointed to the need for continued CSCE activities in his 
republic. 
  According to Snegur, Kishinev [Chisinau] and Tiraspol based 
dialog on the CSCE Moldovan mission's advice for stability in 
Transdniestria. 
  The multi-party elections of 27 March, said Snegur, and the 
victory, in the elections, of a centrist-oriented party, made 
the solution of the Transdniestrian problem possible. 
  Snegur and Richard Samuel met in the runup to next week's 
session of the CSCE's standing council which is to concentrate 
on the extension of the Moldovan mission's mandate. 

</TEXT>

