<F P=100> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev: West Should Help Forward Russia's Reforms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev: West Should Help Forward Russia's Reforms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804112194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1018 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS and KAZTAG special correspondents] </F>
  [Text] Tokyo 8 April, TASS -- The West "should help Russia 
in the process of reforms, democratisation and stabilisation, 
nor for remarks by concrete politicians," President Nursultan 
Nazarbayev of Kazakhstan told a news conference here on Friday. 
[sentence as received] 
  Both Moscow and all its neighbours in the east and west are 
interested in the success of Russian transformations, emphasised 
Nazarbayev, who is currentlty in Japan on an official visit. 
  Nazarbayev believes that there is nothing surprising in the 
complex processes taking place in the former Soviet Union. The 
majority of current problems have been brought about by the 
disintegration of the Soviet Union's economic system and 
break-up of the common ruble area, and should have been foreseen 
by politicians who were busy producing a Commonwealth of 
Independent States in Belovezhskaya Pushcha forest, he said. 

</TEXT>

