<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Completes Visit to Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Completes Visit to Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904144594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1330 GMT 
9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0904144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kazakhstani President Nursultan Nazarbayev has 
completed his visit to Japan. The main purpose of the visit was 
to obtain prearranged credits and to sell his country's 
resources to business circles. In his opinion, this has been 
achieved. As he told ITAR-TASS on his arrival on 6 April, 
Alma-Ata [Almaty] did not set any other tasks. Calling for 
cooperation in the future, Nursultan Nazarbayev, well known for 
his passion for hunting, realized that a bird in the hand is 
worth two in the bush. That is why the securing of Japanese 
promises on credits for $220 million in aid of reforms and 12.88 
trillion yen for the development of the infrastructure were 
described as the main successes of the visit. 

</TEXT>

