<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Quadrilateral Talks on Tajik Refugees Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Quadrilateral Talks on Tajik Refugees Held </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804222094 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 1700 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804222094 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tajik </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the initiative of the United Nations High 
Commission for Refugees [UNHCR], quadrilateral talks were held 
in Termez, Uzbekistan, attended by Tajikistan, Russia, 
Uzbekistan, and the Islamic State of Afghanistan. The speedy 
repatriation of Tajik refugees from Afghanistan were discussed 
at the talks. 
  Summing up the talks, Himmat Davlatov, deputy minister and 
head of the refugees affairs department of the Tajik Ministry of 
Labor and Employment, told the Khovar news agency that he and 
Deputy Foreign Minister Mirzoyev represented Tajikistan at the 
talks. Also present were Zainulobiddinov, consul of the Russian 
Federation in Mazar-e Sharif, Afghanistan; (?Irgachev), 
ambassador on special affairs at the Foreign Affairs Ministry of 
Uzbekistan; and General Sakhi Hashem, deputy to General Dostum 
and representative of northern regions of Afghanistan. 
  Participants in the talks unanimously decided that the 
social 
and political situation in Tajikistan is returning to normal and 
that refugees can return to their permanent places of residence 
without any problems. 
  The UNHCR representative at the talks said that Tajik 
refugees returning home from the Sakhi camp are being given 
three months of food rations. The same humanitarian assistance 
applies to refugees who returning home from Konduz Province in 
Afghanistan. 

</TEXT>

