<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statement: Border Clashes Aimed at Disrupting Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statement: Border Clashes Aimed at Disrupting Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804140594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1045 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Continuing provocations at the Tajik-Afghan border 
are aimed at frustrating the inter-Tajik talks being held in 
Moscow. The statement was made by the chief of the information 
department of the Tajik Foreign Ministry Zafar Saidov at a 
briefing in Dushanbe. 
  He believes that the process of the return of Tajik refugees 
to their homeland is becoming steady. However, this does not 
suit the interests of the armed Tajik opposition and its 
militants are trying to frustrate the process. Saidov said that 
the check point of the Russian border guard troops, was shelled 
in the morning of April 7, from the vicinity of the port of 
Sherkhan (Afghanistan) where about 700 refugees are amassed 
waiting to return to their homeland. 
  Saidov said that the Russian border guards showed restraint 
and did not retaliate. This is another manifestation of who 
wants to restore peace in Tajikistan and who does not, he added. 

</TEXT>

