<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tajikistan Sends Official Note to Afghanistan on Incident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tajikistan Sends Official Note to Afghanistan on Incident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804193394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1906 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tajikistan has sent an official note to Afghanistan 
demanding that the recent incidents on the Tajik-Afghan border 
be investigated and the responsible be punished, a highly placed 
official in the Tajik Foreign Ministry, Zafar Saydov, said at a 
briefing in Dushanbe on Friday. 
  Saydov told journalists about the artillery shooting against 
the Russian border post in the Khatlon Region from Afghan 
territory on April 7. Moreover, he added that a Russian armored 
carrier had been blown up by an anti-tank mine. A border 
officer had been killed. 
  Saydov said he had reliable information proving that these 
actions had been planned before hand and had been carried out 
from Afghan territory. Over the first three months of this year 
several facilities, including the Russian border defenses have 
been subjected to fire from Afghan territory over forty times. 
Casualties and significant material damage have been reported. 
  The Tajik Foreign Ministry's note demanded that appropriate 
strict measures be used against illegal Tajik armed units acting 
on Afghan territory in order to halt their activities, Saydov 
stressed. 

</TEXT>

