<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Stops Gas Deliveries to Azerbaijan 7 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Stops Gas Deliveries to Azerbaijan 7 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804204094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1951 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkmenistan stopped the supply of its gas to 
Azerbaijan as of 10:00 of April 7. Until that time the rate of 
supply was 8 Mn cubic meters a day. Officials of the Azerigaz 
state-owned company told Interfax that the cause was that 
Azerbaijan had not pay the $50 Mn it owed for supplies in the 
first quarter of the year. That amount had to be paid with oil 
products, machinery and consumer goods. The Azeri government 
has not, however, set the export quotas. 
  Turkmenistan was supposed to supply to Azerbaijan 3 Bn cubic 
meters of gas evaluated as $240 Mn. Since the beginning of the 
year 956 Mn cubic meters have been supplied and partly paid for 
in kind. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

