<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baburin Wants Sanctions Lifted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baburin Wants Sanctions Lifted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804152894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1427 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 TASS -- Russian leftist leader Sergey 
Baburin said on Friday that sanctions against Yugoslavia should 
be scrapped. Baburin, a rather influential member of the current 
and last parliaments, leader of the pro-Communist Russian 
National Union, was speaking to reporters after his return from 
Sarajevo, Belgrade and serb Krajina. 
  "It is necessary to boost the efforts of the Russian 
Government, parliament and Foreign Ministry to lift the U.N. 
sanctions against the Union Republic of Yugoslavia and fight for 
a halt to Russia's participation in these sanctions", Baburin 
said, adding that Russia should become more active with its 
humanitarian aid to Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro). 
  Baburin backed the idea of sending more Russian 
peace-keepers 
to Sarajevo, but rejected the idea of sending Turkish units to 
the conflict zone under the aegis of the United Nations. "There 
is a threat of Islamic domination, even of a rebirth of 
fundamentalism (in the Balkans)", he noted. 

</TEXT>

