<H3> <TI>   Commander--No Russian Troops Injured </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commander--No Russian Troops Injured </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104073594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0656 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104073594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 11 Apr -- The Russian Federation servicemen 
carrying out peacekeeping tasks in the Sarajevo area suffered no 
injuries in the air raids by two NATO bombers that on the 
evening of 10 April carried out strikes against Serb positions 
near the Bosnian town of Gorazde. Colonel-General Yevgeniy 
Podkolzin, commander of the air assault troops, informed the 
ITAR-TASS correspondent of this today, citing the morning report 
from commanders of both peacekeeping battalions fulfilling tasks 
in the Balkans. 
  Yevgeniy Podkolzin was very adverse in his response to the 
NATO generals' decision to inflict strikes against civilian 
targets located far from the front line, which have caused to 
casualties. "The Russian Federation soldiers in this conflict 
see their task to be to bring peace to people, not to resort to 
such extreme measures", the commander of the air assault troops 
stressed. 

</TEXT>

