<H3> <TI>   Airlift Suspension Not Discussed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Airlift Suspension Not Discussed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104115294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1046 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The leadership of the Russian Defense Ministry did 
not consider the question of suspending the airlift to the 
former Yugoslavia of an additional contingent of Russian 
peace-keepers due to the NATO air strike against Serb positions 
in the area of Gorazde, INTERFAX was told by the spokesman for 
the Defense Ministry Vladimir Kosarev. 
  He said that a Ukrainian infantry company of the 
peace-keeping contingent is stationed in the vicinity of Gorazde 
where earlier NATO forces bombed the Bosnian Serb positions. 
The spokesman said that there are no casualties among the 
Ukrainian servicemen. 
  Earlier the Federation Council decided to send to the former 
Yugoslavia an additional 300 Russian servicemen to raise the 
number of the Russian contingent to 1500 people. 

</TEXT>

