<H3> <TI>   Liberal Democrats Denounce Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liberal Democrats Denounce Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104115094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1122 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The Russian Liberal-Democratic Party denounces the 
air strike against the Serb positions near the town of Gorazde 
by the UN armed forces," says the party's Supreme Council 
statement spread in the State Duma Monday. The statement says 
that similar actions "destabilize the situation in the Balkans, 
internationalize the conflict, which is the internal affair of 
the state structures formed on the basis of the former republics 
of Yugoslavia." 
  The statement says that the world wars of the 20th Century 
were unleashed in the Balkans and adds that the "Russian people 
support their Serb brothers." 
  Liberal Democratic party chairman Vladimir Zhirinovskiy is 
currently in Strasburg where the Russian parliamentary 
delegation takes part in the parliamentary assembly of the 
Council of Europe. 

</TEXT>

