<H3> <TI>   Navy Command Protests Ukrainian Seizure of Fleet Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Navy Command Protests Ukrainian Seizure of Fleet Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104104794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1019 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 11 TASS -- The main command of the 
Russian Navy resolutely protested against the seizure by 
Ukrainian commandos of a unit of the Black Sea Fleet stationed 
near Odessa. 
  "Such actions can be interpreted only as political 
irresponsibility and deliberate ignoring of the 
Russian-Ukrainian agreements reached in Yalta and Massandra", 
the press service of the Navy told TASS on Monday qualifying the 
events as "provocative". 
  "The actions of the Ukrainian side are provocative in 
essence 
and form, are a flagrant violation of the reached agreements and 
create an explosive situation on the Black Sea Fleet", the press 
service said. 
  120 Ukrainian commandos from a special task force seized 
late 
on Sunday a division of the Black Sea Fleet, including its coast 
facilities, the communication centre, the premises containing 
secret documents and weapons. Commander of the unit Captain 
First Rank Oleg Feoktistov and Commander of the coast units 
Captain Second Rank Dmitriy Starikov were arrested, handcuffed 
and taken to the military commandant's office. Chief of staff 
Captain Second Rank Aleksandr Zelenko was also arrested. 
Navymen and members of their families were beaten during the 
attack. 
  "Who could have ordered such actions against a military unit 
making part of the Black Sea Fleet which is subordinated to the 
presidents of Russia and Ukraine?", the press service asked and 
added that most indignation is caused by brutalities of 
Ukrainian commandos towards family members of navymen. 

</TEXT>

