<F P=102>   LD0904145094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1400 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 9 (TASS) -- "Ukrainian border guards 
were overexcited with patriotism," Head of the Black Sea Fleet 
Press Center Andrey Grachev told ITAR-TASS here today, 
commenting on the Odessa conflict of Russian seamen with 
Ukrainian border guards. 
  In his words, the Russian Cheleken military vessel arrived 
in 
Odessa to load hydrographic equipment and carry it to 
Sevastopol. However, last night Ukrainian border guards tried to 
prevent this and even placed armed guards near the ship. Their 
actions almost provoked a serious conflict. 
  In the opinion of Grachev, Ukrainian military are 
responsible 
for the attempt to hamper the planned transportation of Russian 
property for repairs. He stressed that the Russian hydrographic 
vessel which has a military crew shall not be liable for customs 
and border inspection. There are no documents to prohibit such 
actions in the Black Sea Fleet's operational zone. 

</TEXT>

