<H3> <TI>   Israeli Plane Forced Down at Sochi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Plane Forced Down at Sochi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104101894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1005 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104101894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 11 TASS -- Fighters of the Russian 
airforce forced to land an Israeli "Gulfstream-159" plane flying 
from Tbilisi, Georgia, to Tel Aviv after it had violated the 
rules of crossing the Russian border and using the national 
airspace, spokesman of the Russian Air Defence Leonid Shirobokov 
told TASS on Monday. 
  The incident occurred on Saturday when the plane entered the 
Russian airspace to the south-east of the city of Mineralnye 
Vody without a preliminary request and permission from 
authorities. 
  The plane ignored the demands of Russian authorities to 
return back to the airport of departure and continued the 
flight. Russian airforce fighters then intercepted the plane 
and forced it to land in Adler, the airport of Sochi. 

</TEXT>

