<H3> <TI>   Latvia Rejects Clarifications of Yeltsin Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latvia Rejects Clarifications of Yeltsin Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804202794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1719 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Latvia will not accept Moscow's clarifications about 
President Yeltsin's decree 174 of April 5 because of its 
sovereignty being put under threat, Latvian Embassy officials 
told Interfax. They referred to Friday's statement that Latvian 
ambassador Janis Peters made to Russian Deputy Foreign Minister 
Vitaliy Churkin. 
  President Yeltsin on Thursday issued a decree supporting 
proposals by the defence and foreign ministries to set up 
Russian military bases in other CIS states and Latvia. 
Officials of both ministries later spoke of "technical 
mistakes" being made in drafting the paper and Russian 
Ambassador to Riga Aleksandr Rannikh made a formal apology to 
the Latvian Foreign Ministry. 
  Latvian Embassy officials said Churkin had suggested that 
the 
two countries should maintain their relations as usual working 
on the assumption that the Yeltsin decree did not exist. He was 
also quoted as having promised a thorough investigation into the 
origin of the paper "which is out of line with bilateral 
agreements, already initialled." 

</TEXT>

