<H3> <TI>   Russia To Consult CIS on Bases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia To Consult CIS on Bases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804132294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1222 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kochuk] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev denied the existence of a presidential resolution 
about military bases in the CIS which had appeared in the press, 
but said the document is being drafted. 
  The document is being drafted and positions of CIS countries 
and of the "near abroad" will be (undoubtedly) taken into 
consideration, Kozyrev said after talks with his Columbian 
counterpart Nohemi Sanin Posada de Rubio. The "near abroad" 
includes all former Soviet republics. 
  "The issue of deploying Russian military bases will be 
discussed only with those countries which display such an 
interest", the Russian foreign minister said. 

