<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baltic Fleet Denies Selling Radioactive Hovercraft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baltic Fleet Denies Selling Radioactive Hovercraft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904130894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0400 GMT 
9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0904130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The press center of the Baltic Fleet has described 
as completely untrue reports in some of the media that the 
command of the Baltic Fleet's Tallinn base has illegally sold to 
local commercial bodies a number of out-of-service hover landing 
craft containing sources of radioactive radiation. 
  The fact of the matter is that, after receiving permission 
from higher authority, the command of Tallinn naval base agreed 
in February 1993 to hand over two redundant minesweepers for 
scrapping and subsequent sale to the Estonian (Bankir) company. 
The terms of the agreement have been observed by both sides. 
There were no sources of radioactive radiation on the 
minesweepers. Moreover, ships of the type in question are not 
designed to carry such installations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

