<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement on Principles Signed With Colombia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreement on Principles Signed With Colombia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804131694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1240 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Gennadiy Kochuk] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 8 TASS -- An agreement on principles of 
relations between the Russian Federation and Colombia was signed 
on Friday by the two countries' ministers of foreign affairs 
Andrey Kozyrev and Nohemi Sanin Posada de Rubio. The signing 
took place in the Russian Foreign Ministry's mansion in downtown 
Moscow within the framework of bilateral talks conducted by the 
Colombian minister in Russia. The agreement which the two 
ministers signed today is the first document of its kind in 
relations between Russia and Latin American countries. 
  The agreement is most important for Russia's global and 
bilateral relations with the countries of the Latin American 
continent, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev said after 
the signing. The Colombia minister of foreign affairs for her 
part stressed the fact that Colombia opens a new page in 
relations between Russia and Latin American countries. She 
expressed the hope that her country would soon become a stable 
partner of Russia's in a variety of sphere, including 
scientific, technological, cultural and trade cooperation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

