<F P=106> [Report by Ridvan Sapmaz] </F>
  [Text] Baku--The CIS Interparliamentary Assembly 
delegation, which is continuing contacts in the region to find a 
solution to the Azerbaijani-Armenian conflict, has resubmitted a 
proposal to set up 36 military garrisons in Karabakh and grant 
them the status of a military base. President Geydar Aliyev 
rejected the proposal. 
