<H3> <TI>   Group Opposes Return of Russian Troops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Group Opposes Return of Russian Troops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0804190594 Baku TURAN in English 1145 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0804190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (April 8) TURAN--"Democratic Congress is deeply 
concerned about return of Russian troops in Azerbaijan", says 
the statement distributed yesterday in Baku. 
  The statement says that the return of Russian troops will 
not 
help to settle the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict. 
  Democratic Congress considers that the priority in the 
settlement of the conflict should be given to the UNO and the 
CSCE organizations, but not to the efforts of one state. 
Democratic Congress mentions that Azerbaijan's conservative 
forces can make use of the return of Russian troops and it can 
lead to tragic consequences. Democratic Congress says that it 
will use all democratic means to prevent the return of Russian 
troops in Azerbaijan. 
  The statement was distributed due to resolution of Russian 
President concerning the creation of military bases of the 
Russian army on the territory of the CIS. Earlier Russian 
Defense Minister, Pavel Grachev, said that Russia intends to 
create one military base in Azerbaijan as well. 
  Democratic Congress was founded on March 23 by the 
opposition 
parties of the country. It includes Democratic Party, the 
Popular [People's] Front, "Ana Torpag" party and the party of 
Nation's Freedom. 

</TEXT>

