<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source': Baku Has no Plans To Withdraw from CIS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source': Baku Has no Plans To Withdraw from CIS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004164494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1515 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1004164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] All speculations about Azerbaijan's plans to 
withdraw from the CIS, to be announced during the CIS summit on 
April 15, are unfounded, an informed source in the Azerbaijani 
president staff told Interfax, commenting on an article in the 
Moscow newspaper Kommersant (April 8, 1994). 
  "The authors seem to be engaged in wishful thinking. In 
actual fact, Baku's policies differ cardinally form what is said 
in the article. We are planning to work for putting into 
operation the CIS mechanism of curbing external and internal 
aggressors," he said. 

</TEXT>

