<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Details </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Details </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904212494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2057 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Schegoleva] </F>
  [Text] Sochi April 10 TASS -- The first meeting of the 
commission for voluntary return of refugees and displaced 
persons to Abkhazia ended late on Saturday night in Sochi. The 
meeting was held in accordance with the four-side agreement 
signed in Moscow on April 4. A statement adopted at the meeting 
stated the discussion of a program of the commission work, 
including the activities of experts on specific issues. 
  The sides agreed that a mission of the U.N. High Commission 
for Refugees [UNHCR] will come on a working visit to the 
Abkhazian Gali region and areas of temporary accommodation of 
displaced persons "in order to prepare the arrangements on the 
return of refugees and displaced persons". The visit will be 
held before the second meeting of the commission scheduled for 
April 26. 
  The sides confirmed their readiness to abide by principles 
and provisions of the Moscow agreement on voluntary return of 
refugees and displaced persons, proceeding from the fact that 
the return of refugees will be related to the deployment of 
peace-making forces. At the same time, the sides believes that 
preparations for the return of refugees and displaced persons 
must begin immediately. 
  The statement was signed by head of the Georgian State 
committee for Refugees Valeriy Vashakidze, first deputy chairman 
of the Abkhazian Council of Ministers Leonid Lakerbaya, head of 
the Russian Federal Migration Service Nikolay Chulkov and Anton 
Vervey on behalf of the office of the U.N. High Commission for 
Refugees. 

</TEXT>

