<H3> <TI>   Further Details </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Details </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0904114694 Yerevan SNARK in English 0536 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0904114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, April 9 (SNARK) -- Three people are killed 
and one is seriously wounded as a result of the explosion under 
the last carriage of the Yerevan-Tbilisi passenger train. As 
SNARK was told in the information center of the Emergency 
Situations Department of the Republic of Armenia, the tragedy 
took place today at 3 a.m. during the customs examination of the 
train at Sadakhlo station (Georgia). The explosion brought 
about a fire that affected the adjacent carriages. Luckily, the 
passengers had managed to evacuate. 
  The contact wire at that part of the railway is damaged. It 
is already being reconstructed. The victims were taken to the 
hospital of the frontier town Noiemberian [spelling as received]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

