BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, April 9 (SNARK) -- The representatives of 
the Georgian authorities and a special investigating group of 
the Georgian Home Affairs Department left today for the Sadakhlo 
station where the Tbilisi-Yerevan train No. 675 was exploded at 
3:00 a.m. The Head of the Transport Department of the Georgian 
National Security Department Colonel Ivan Kuldjanishvili told 
SNARK three passengers were killed and 5 wagons burnt as a 
result of explosion. The investigation has started. 

</TEXT>

