<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   TURAN Blames Ethnic Strife </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TURAN Blames Ethnic Strife </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0904200294 Baku TURAN in English 1628 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0904200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (April 9) TURAN -- Three people were killed 
when a blast ripped through a passenger train in Southern 
Georgia,on Saturday. 
  The train on its way from Tbilisi to the Armenian capital 
Yerevan, was standing in the station at the Azerbaijani border 
town Sadakhlo in the early hours of the morning when the 
explosion occurred. Two man and a woman died and a child was 
seriously injured in the blast, which sparked a blaze that 
destroyed three cars. 
  TURAN news agency was informed from the informed sources 
that 
it was likely the blast had been caused by a terrorist act. 
Several trains have been blown up by bombs and in the last five 
years in the Transcaucasus region, rent by ethnic conflicts. 

</TEXT>

