<H3> <TI>   Police Disperses Gamsakhurdia Supporter Rally </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Disperses Gamsakhurdia Supporter Rally </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904133594 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1300 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi 9 April -- An Iberia news agency 
correspondent reports that representatives of the Round Table 
political bloc [supporters of former President Zviad 
Gamsakhurdia] gathered near the Philharmonic Concert Hall today 
at 1300 hours and attempted to hold an unauthorized rally. The 
police dispersed the gathered. Several people were arrested. 
Some of the ralliers marched peacefully towards Rustaveli 
Prospekt to lay flowers at the memorial to those killed on 9 
April [day in 1989 Soviet troops dispersed a peaceful rally 
killing 20 people]. By 1400 hours about 2,000 supporters of the 
former Georgian President Zviad Gamsakhurdia approached the 
House of Government with the intention of holding a rally there. 
The area in front of the Government House was guarded by some 
500 policemen led by Gela Lanchava. 
  The ralliers then went to the Mtatsminda Pantheon and paid 
homage to Merab Kostava. 

</TEXT>

