<DOCNO> FBIS4-15605 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov069_e_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-069 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reporting on Black Sea Fleet Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reporting on Black Sea Fleet Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kiev Cites `Terrorist Act' </H4>

<F P=102> LD0904191394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1800 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0904191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 9 April, Anatoliy Kovalyov, counsellor-minister 
of the Russian Embassy in Kiev, was summoned to the Ukrainian 
Foreign Affairs Ministry. A note of protest was handed to him 
in connection with the illegitimate actions of the Russian 
survey vessel Cheleken in the vicinity of Odessa. On the night 
of 8-9 April, in gross violation of international law, it 
resorted to violence with the threat of arms and illegally 
seized hydrographic and navigational equipment belonging to 
Ukraine. The fact that people's lives were endangered is 
grounds to qualify these actions of the command of the Russian 
vessel as an international terrorist act. It was only due to 
the balanced stand of the Ukrainian guard that bloodshed was 
prevented. The irony of this bandit action deserves special 
attention. It was carried out on the eve of the celebrations in 
connection with the 50th anniversary of Odessa's liberation from 
the German fascist invaders. 
  The Ukrainian side demands that the seized property of 
Ukraine be returned immediately and those guilty be severely 
punished. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

