<H3> <TI>   Reporting on Black Sea Fleet Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reporting on Black Sea Fleet Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ukrainian Troops Storm Unit </H4>

<F P=102> LD1104062594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0615 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104062594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 11 TASS -- Commander of the Black Sea 
Fleet Admiral Eduard Baltin has described as "actions of 
uncontrollable gangs" the act of provocation which occurred in 
Odessa on Sunday night, when some 120 Ukrainian commandoes 
stormed the Black Sea Fleet's local conservation division. 
  According to Andrey Grachev, the chief of the Black Sea 
Fleet 
press centre, the storming was conducted from 21:00 to 23:00 
[1700 to 1900 GMT] on [10] April. The Ukrainian storm troopers 
arrested Russsian officers Oleg Feoktistov, Dmitriy Starikov and 
Aleksandr Zelyonka. According to the source, the Russian naval 
officers were handcuffed, although their only "offence" was that 
they remained loyal to the oath of allegiance they gave once. 
The other officers and midshipmen of the division were blocked 
by Ukrainian commandoes inside the division base. 
  Grachev said the Ukrainian Navy commander Vladimir 
Beskorovainy was aboard the commandship Slavutich in Odessa at 
the time and his complicity in the action was, according to 
Grachev, beyond doubt. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

