<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reporting on Black Sea Fleet Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reporting on Black Sea Fleet Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Russian Sailors Said Wounded </H4>

<F P=102> LD1104075394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0720 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104075394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 11 TASS -- There are wounded among the 
personnel and children of Russian sailors as a result of an 
assault of the Conservation Division of the Black Sea Fleet, 
deployed in Odessa, by the Ukrainian Special Task Force in the 
evening of April 10. Windows were smashed in the premises of 
the unit, the civilians working there were beaten up and 
transported to the populated locality of Chabana, suburb of 
Odessa, ITAR-TASS learned today in the morning from Andrey 
Grachev, head of the press centre of the Black Sea Fleet. 
  According to Grachev, the room where the division's weapons 
were kept, as well as premises of the secret and financial 
services, were sealed and are now being guarded by the Ukrainian 
Special Task Force. 
  Commander of the Black Sea Fleet Eduard Baltin described the 
incident as "actions of uncontrollable gangs". Russian sailors 
cannot understand how Ukrainian soldiers can be so malicious and 
cruel to their Slavonic brothers. They displayed utmost cruelty 
during the capture of the division of the Black Sea Fleet. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

