<H4>    No Communications With Fleet Unit </H4>

<F P=102> LD1104094594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0926 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol April 11 TASS -- It is impossible to 
contact Russian servicemen from the Black Sea Fleet unit which 
was stormed by Ukrainian commandos late on Sunday [10 April] as 
communications with the 46th Hydrographic Division of the fleet 
situated near Odessa have been disrupted. 
  The fleet command is working to stabilise the situation, 
spokesman of the Black Sea Fleet Andrey Grachev told TASS on 
Monday. He did not elaborate. 

</TEXT>

