<H3> <TI>   Zlenko's Turkish Visit Deemed `Quite Successful' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zlenko's Turkish Visit Deemed `Quite Successful' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804221594 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1630 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804221594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, As UNIAN reported earlier, Ukraine's Foreign 
Minister Anatoliy Zlenko was in Turkey on 7 April on a one-day 
official visit. In the opinion of Ukraine's Foreign Ministry 
officials, the visit was quite successful. Ways to intensify 
bilateral economic relations were discussed. According to the 
Foreign Ministry, the two sides attach particularly great 
importance to the interaction within the Black Sea Economic 
Cooperation framework, especially the fulfilment of bilateral 
and multilateral cooperation projects in investments, first of 
all in the sphere of infrastructure modernization and 
integration in sea, automobile, and air transport. 
  Turkey is looking for access to the Ukrainian market and 
proposes cooperation in such spheres as metallurgy and metal 
work, food processing, ship-building, carriage and bus 
construction, textiles, sewn goods, cellulose and paper, mining, 
coal, chemical and petrochemical industries. 

</TEXT>

