<H3> <TI>   Official Denies Report on Unsafe Uranium Processing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Denies Report on Unsafe Uranium Processing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804172294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1637 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [By UKRINFORM correspondent Sergey Kravchenko] 
  [Text] Kiev April 8 -- Deputy head of the Ukrainian 
Environmental Ministry's Nuclear and Radiation Safety department 
Konstantin Rudya categorically refuted today press reports 
claiming Ukrainian extraction and processing of uranium is not 
controlled. 
  "Some would like to force Ukraine out from the uranium 
market 
and make an impression things do not go smoothly in this 
sphere," he said. "In fact, the branch has its problems both in 
Ukraine, Russia, Estonia and other former Soviet republics, the 
problems which were inherited from the semi-classified Soviet 
Ministry of Medium Machine-Building." Rudya stressed the 
republic is correcting the past mistakes. For instance, it is 
creating a system of early warning radiation control and much 
better decontaminates the environment, dumps and tailing dumps 
in the areas of uranium workings. 

</TEXT>

