<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Stetsyuk for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol April 11 TASS - The command of the 
Ukrainian Navy has issued an appeal to the Crimean leadership, 
urging to "protect the military from political games." The 
document said that "Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov is counting 
on the Black Sea Fleet in putting into effect the results of the 
survey, held in the Crimean Peninsula on March 27." The command 
of the Ukrainian Navy is concerned over a possible drawing of 
the armed forces into the implementation of the reform in the 
Crimea. The appeal stressed that the Black Sea Fleet is 
subordinated to the Ukrainian and Russian presidents and that 
citizens of the two fraternal countries are serving there. 

