<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Bloc Wins Election to Crimean Parliament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Bloc Wins Election to Crimean Parliament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104084894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0625 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol, 11 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- The Russia Bloc, 
which supports the strengthening of the peninsula's links with 
the Russian Federation, has won an overwhelming victory in the 
elections to the Crimean Supreme Soviet. The second round of 
voting was held on Sunday. 
  Viktor Alsufyev, chairman of the republic's Central 
Electoral 
Commission, said at a news conference in Simferopol this morning 
that 54 out of the 94 seats in the parliament went to the Russia 
Bloc. Four seats remain vacant. 
  Yuriy Meshkov, president of the Republic of Crimea, said in 
an interview with an ITAR-TASS correspondent that the Russia 
Bloc's victory is confirmation of support for the aims and tasks 
declared by the electoral bloc. 
  The first session of the new Crimean parliament will be held 
May 10. 
  It was also announced at a news conference that the 
inhabitants of Crimea have taken part in elections to the 
Ukrainian Supreme Soviet. Eleven deputies from Crimea out of 23 
were elected. 

</TEXT>

